haas center for public service letter from the faculty director student affairs haas center for public service students faculty alumni community about stanford university student affairs all stanford search submit letter from the faculty director letter from the faculty director haas center for public service information donor as the new faculty co directors of the haas center for public service appointed in its 25 th anniversary year we are honored to be helping to guide the future of education for global citizenship and community engagement at stanford we come to the job from different disciplinary perspectives but we share a passion and commitment to inspiring and preparing the next generation to assume leadership roles in public service as undergraduates these young people are given extraordinary opportunities at the haas center to learn through guided service in east palo alto schools environmental nonprofits and government agencies in sacramento federal offices in washington dc and ngos around the globe in significant numbers our students take those experiences and shape them into lifelong commitments to careers and lives of service our 2010 2015 strategic plan has clarified fresh and exciting priorities for the next five years that require new resources to achieve we rely on you our stalwart friends including thousands of alumni to help us remain a strong clear voice for public service at stanford we cannot do this work without you you can help us move forward with gifts of any size but we ask that you consider making a special gift this year of unrestricted support please be as generous as you can so that we can apply new funds to these emerging priorities the stakes have never been higher nor the work of the haas center more urgent or meaningful please explore options to make a gift online you may also contact suzanne abel for more information about the ways to support our work thank you larry diamond and julie kennedy peter e haas co directors make a gift 